A man who holed himself up six storeys above the ground in a crane in Richards Bay has reportedly come down and given himself up to police.It was original thought to be a hostage situation with two people on the crane but this has been revised to one.While details are still sketchy Richard Schouten of IPSS Medical Rescue said earlier that police including hostage negotiators and paramedics were at Lira Link near the Boardwalk Inkwazi Shopping Centre early on Monday morning. Hostage situation. Two persons barricaded in tower crane 6 floors up IPSS and SAPS hostage negotiation team busy trying to establish contact he said via WhatsApp.This is a developing story and will be updated. TMG Digital/The Times 